com.ozdevworx.dtype.impl

Class SqlList

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ozdevworx.dtype.impl.SqlList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    LabelledArray

    public class SqlList
extends java.lang.Object
implements LabelledArray
    A List based array. Access LabelledArrays Data via a String label or a numeric index.
    A LabelledArray is an Object itself so support for multidimensional LabelledArray Objects is generic to this implementation.

    This implementation uses synchronization as specified by the LabelledArray interface.

    The synchronization abilities for ArrayList is handled by this class as ArrayList is not a synchronized Object by default.

    Handles sql NULL and java null better than previous LabelledArray implementations.
    Version:
    2010-04-26 added sql NULL to java null conversions, 2010-04-28 added numeric conversion for values of Java null to 0., 2010-05-07 improved synchronization.
    Author:
    Tim Gall

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      SqlList()
      Create a case sensitive LabelledArray of initial capacity 10.
      Initial capacity is 10 with an expansion rate of 10 when the LabelledArray is growing.
      Empty place holders are ignored when manipulating and querying data.

      EG:
      length() returns the actual size and does not include placeholders related to this LabelledArrays growth rate.
      isEmpty() does not count placeholders, only actual Elements that were added to the LabelledArray.
      etc.
      SqlList(boolean lowerCaseKeys)

      isEmpty() does not count placeholders, only actual Elements that were added to the LabelledArray.

      • SqlList

        public SqlList()
        Create a case sensitive LabelledArray of initial capacity 10.
        Initial capacity is 10 with an expansion rate of 10 when the LabelledArray is growing.
        Empty place holders are ignored when manipulating and querying data.

        EG:
        length() returns the actual size and does not include placeholders related to this LabelledArrays growth rate.
        isEmpty() does not count placeholders, only actual Elements that were added to the LabelledArray.
        etc.

      • SqlList

        public SqlList(boolean lowerCaseKeys)
        Create a case insensitive LabelledArray of initial capacity incSize.
        Initial capacity is 10 with an expansion rate of 10 when the LabelledArray is growing.
        Empty place holders are ignored when manipulating and querying data.

        EG:
        getSize() returns the actual Element count and does not include placeholders related to this LabelledArrays growth rate.
        isEmpty() does not count placeholders, only actual Elements that were added to the LabelledArray.
        etc.
        Parameters:
        lowerCaseKeys - boolean. If true, keys all use lower case, if false keys all use upper case.

      • SqlList

        public SqlList(int incSize)
        Create a case sensitive LabelledArray of initial capacity incSize.
        Initial capacity is incSize with an expansion rate of incSize when the LabelledArray is growing.
        Empty place holders are ignored when manipulating and querying data.

        EG:
        getSize() returns the actual Element count and does not include placeholders related to this LabelledArrays growth rate.
        isEmpty() does not count placeholders, only actual Elements that were added to the LabelledArray.
        etc.
        Parameters:
        incSize - int. This value affects the initial size and the expansion rate when the LabelledArray is growing.
